claim.claim-text:
8. A method for reducing odd harmonics in an alternating current supply, comprising: 
receiving a user command to control a load; 
determining a phase angle at each zero crossing of the alternating current supply required to implement the user command; 
identifying a predetermined range of phase angles to modulate around; 
not modifying the phase angle if the phase angle is less than the predetermined range of phase angles; 
modifying the phase angle by performing one of selectively adding and selectively subtracting a predetermined phase from the phase angle if the phase angle is within the predetermined range of phase angles; 
calculating an error in response to modifying the phase angle; 
adding the error to a subsequent phase angle so that an average phase angle equals required phase angle modification required to implement the user command; and 
not modifying the phase angle if the phase angle is greater than the predetermined range of phase angles.
